ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It was a very helpful, educational, and enjoyable course and I would highly recommend it.

I would definitely recommend it to another student. I really appreciated not being slammed with a giant final at the end of the course. Instead, I really liked that the work was evenly distributed throughout the semester.
Great class with lots of information, very interesting, would definitely recommend.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I hadn't taken any courses in Developmental biology so this was a good introduction.
The papers, selected for discussion were always excellent! They were progressive and thought provoking.
I liked learning all of the information about development. At the time I was rotating in a developmental lab so the information was invaluable.
